title: Dentisociaria armata
text:
Dentisociaria armata is a species of <a href="moth">moth</a> of the family <a href="Tortricidae">Tortricidae</a>. It is found in the <a href="Russian%20Far%20East">Russian Far East</a> (Amur, Primorsky Krai), <a href="China">China</a> and <a href="Japan">Japan</a>. The habitat consists of broad-leaved forests, but the species has also been observed in inhabited areas such as parks.
The <a href="wingspan">wingspan</a> is 15–23 mm. Adults have been recorded on wing from July to September.
